<TITLE> Manchester United win Community Shield on penalties </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Premier League champions Manchester United beat FA Cup winners Chelsea 3-0 on penalties to win the Community Shield in a shootout on Sunday. Stalwart Ryan Giggs gave United a 35th minute lead with a sweetly-struck shot but Chelsea's new France winger Florent Malouda levelled with a fine solo goal on the stroke of halftime. Neither side created a clear-cut chance after the break, leaving the traditional curtain-raiser for the English top-flight to be settled by a shootout in front of a crowd of more than 80,000 at Wembley. Wayen Rooney struck the winning penalty to give his side first blood in what is expected to be another season-long battle between the two clubs for domestic honours
